To identify pathways enriched for age-related transcriptomic changes in planarians, we performed functional GSEA69 on a pre-ranked list of genes based on their log-transformed P values, corrected by the sign of regulation, calculated as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$-\left({\mathrm{pv}}\right)\times \mathrm{sgn}\left({\mathrm{slope}}\right),$$\end{document}−pv×sgnslope,where ‘pv’ and ‘slope’ are the P value and age-associated slope of expression for a certain gene, respectively, obtained from the edgeR output, and ‘sgn’ is the signum function (equal to 1, −1 or 0 if the value is positive, negative or equal to 0, respectively). REACTOME, KEGG and HALLMARK ontologies from the Molecular Signature Database were utilized as gene sets for GSEA. The fgsea package in R was used to run the GSEA algorithm with 5,000 permutations. An adjusted P-value cutoff of 0.1 was applied to select statistically significant functions.
